You paid more taxes than General Electric in Bank of America. Corporations pay 6.6% of the federal budget.

01:58:09.000 --> 01:58:21.000
The masses out of income tax and payroll taxes contribute 84%. And now they are laying off the public sector so the revenues will decrease.

01:58:21.000 --> 01:58:28.000
We have a $15 trillion debt. We pay a trillion dollars, an interest on the debt which is never discussed.

01:58:28.000 --> 01:58:36.000
So what do they do with all this discussion yesterday and today about Geithner and the G20?

01:58:36.000 --> 01:58:44.000
All the fed is like a monopoly game. Print money, print money, print money, print money but it cannot last.

01:58:44.000 --> 01:58:52.000
And so what do you, the people who understand that it cannot last? What happens when the dollar is no longer the international reserve currency?

01:58:53.000 --> 01:59:09.000
What happens? If this cannot last unless and the jobs are not coming back, the three million jobs are not coming back when you subsidize corporations to export jobs.

01:59:10.000 --> 01:59:23.000
The system is so corrupt. You have (likely) ALEC and politicians. They've written 800 laws.

01:59:23.000 --> 01:59:27.000
There's nobody in Congress writing laws for the public interest.

01:59:28.000 --> 01:59:45.000
And so when you ask about black studies, we are now in a different era because America was built upon the exploitation of the confiscation of Indian land and the exploitation of black labor until the industrial society.

01:59:45.000 --> 01:59:56.000
So immigrants, white immigrants could come and they could get these jobs. But now they exploit new tools.

01:59:58.000 --> 02:00:09.000
So I mean this is the problem. There's no real discussion of the real problems and therefore there's no real solutions being put forward.

02:00:09.000 --> 02:00:20.000
Just print more money or because the same people have the same perspective globally as here in America. The only solution they have is so-called austerity.

02:00:21.000 --> 02:00:35.000
That means screw the public sector with that cannot work. So we have white family income. Black people are disposable. We are now irrelevant.

02:00:36.000 --> 02:00:50.000
And increasingly large in numbers of white people are now economically irrelevant. And they don't care about education. The Reagan came to office. They wanted to get rid of the Department of Education.

02:00:50.000 --> 02:01:02.000
All they care about is privatizing education as they privatize prisons as they want to privatize social security as they want to privatize every bush privatize 25% of the IRS which people don't know.

02:01:03.000 --> 02:01:17.000
So I had a grad student and they audited her. She made $22,000. They audited her. They know audit but as Buffett said they know audit. And they didn't audit. We now find out the SEC destroyed 9,000 documents of investigation.

02:01:17.000 --> 02:01:26.000
We now find out that the General Counsel of the SEC had $2 million invested in it made off. Corruption with a capital K.

02:01:27.000 --> 02:01:45.000
So how do we and what have they done? We ask about Obama. Obama is irrelevant because they have infiltrated all of the ABC. The Foxes are in the Hen House, in the SEC, in the NLRB, in the FAA.

02:01:45.000 --> 02:01:56.000
You flew here in a plane 35 years old, monitored by air traffic control system also 35 years old. And they privatized the subcontractors to take care of the planes.

02:01:57.000 --> 02:02:16.000
Now, everywhere you look there is corruption and money over ours. But these people are different historically because one can make a case that slavery is logical.

02:02:17.000 --> 02:02:30.000
One can make a case that feudalism is logical. But these forces, they have let loose forces that they cannot control and they don't care about the ozone depletion.

02:02:30.000 --> 02:02:40.000
So and you have a clown like (Texas Governor) Rick Perry who doesn't believe in climate change while 78% of his state is on fire and the drought and cows are dying.

02:02:41.000 --> 02:02:51.000
These people are mad. We are in the hands of idiots and maniacs and racist corruption. And I ask, I do not understand why there is not a revolution in this country.

02:02:54.000 --> 02:03:09.000
But there is no opposition that will explain to people what are the problems and what must be done. That's why as I say about black people, just because our cars is just like the Indians does not mean we will triumph.

02:03:11.000 --> 02:03:27.000
And America is going steadily. People all around the world, America's lost its credibility. We are on the wrong side of every question.

02:03:28.000 --> 02:03:40.000
It's unbelievable. But the American people, what are the watching reality television and Fox News and Shrek too?

02:03:40.000 --> 02:03:45.000
It's Shrek. It's a Shrek fire, no. Right.

02:03:46.000 --> 02:04:05.000
We are back on it and during the quick break, Bill wanted to ask you just to stretch out and say a little bit more about the rationale and the argument that led you to move white women out of the project of urban organizing.

02:04:06.000 --> 02:04:24.000
Well, the singing of the wobbly songs, that was their legacy. That was their notion of politics. But you cannot, but you don't drink wine with people whom you are organizing.

02:04:25.000 --> 02:04:35.000
It's just like you don't have sexual relations with people whom you are organizing. Although there were some people who believed that you had makeup with everybody.

02:04:35.000 --> 02:04:46.000
I agree with them as well. It's good looking when we saw you across the, not in our thing, but a SNCC person, a SCLC person who was James Bevel.

02:04:47.000 --> 02:04:58.000
Who's predilections of, you know, who expose at the end of his life, terrible revelations about Bevel.

02:04:58.000 --> 02:05:07.000
So, and taking them down to the east side, then you have to go back to Harlem.

02:05:08.000 --> 02:05:10.000
Down to the people who were organizing back to the Harlem songies.

02:05:10.000 --> 02:05:19.000
Down to the people who were like, go look up after this, who peed a button with the ones. They are exposing them to something that has nothing to do with struggle.

02:05:20.000 --> 02:05:31.000
Well, that's kind of where the song was born. The radical chic where the white campus would take into all the east side parties.

02:05:32.000 --> 02:05:37.000
You can raise funds for these, you know, that's a similar kind of pension.

02:05:37.000 --> 02:05:42.000
Well, I had a problem with the panthers.

02:05:48.000 --> 02:05:54.000
Because actually it was the white left in the European left that is lionized, lionized the panthers.

02:05:55.000 --> 02:06:05.000
Which is not to say some of them. But I have guys who, because as we said before about the relationship between the black community and the police,

02:06:05.000 --> 02:06:12.000
to confront the police, to try and organize against the police is quite logical and was important.

02:06:12.000 --> 02:06:20.000
But they got friends of mine who in the Jersey City BPP, they got killed, cops just like they killed Fred Hampton and Mark Clark.

02:06:21.000 --> 02:06:29.000
So that if you're going to speak as an ex-marine, if you're going to take on the enemy, understand what you're doing.

02:06:29.000 --> 02:06:39.000
You don't announce, hello, I'm going to be out at 430 right now, that we're creating and we're going to get you or we're going to pretend to get you.

02:06:39.000 --> 02:06:51.000
So people don't understand what a real confrontation with the police would entail.

02:06:51.000 --> 02:06:59.000
As I said, I was in the, if I had had my platoon in Detroit, we could have taken over the city.

02:06:59.000 --> 02:07:03.000
Because the cops were shooting each other. They didn't know what they were doing.

02:07:03.000 --> 02:07:15.000
We could have taken over the city, we couldn't have held it, but we could have taken it for a day, for a day and a half.

02:07:15.000 --> 02:07:30.000
But the, just like, there is no theory of change in America because America is the best of all possible worlds.

02:07:30.000 --> 02:07:35.000
All we have are blips that we can correct a little blip here, a little bit there.

02:07:35.000 --> 02:07:40.000
But there's no concept that the whole, as Martin said, that the whole thing must be done away with.

02:07:40.000 --> 02:07:44.000
So we have yet to have, when people may talk about Marxism, we talk about this and that.

02:07:44.000 --> 02:07:49.000
But we've yet to develop, and that's something that Malcolm X was working on.

02:07:49.000 --> 02:07:58.000
Something that the Boggses was laying out. But Malcolm X was working on, how do you really affect change in this country?

02:07:58.000 --> 02:08:04.000
He put forward, as I wrote it, and he put forward two things, internationally and internationally.

02:08:04.000 --> 02:08:14.000
Valorant of the bullet was the national strategy, but hooking up with the, and exposing to the UN and elsewhere, hooking up with, was the international struggles.

02:08:14.000 --> 02:08:23.000
He was invited, he was invited to Algeria in March of 65.

02:08:24.000 --> 02:08:35.000
He's been a he and Che, been well-invited them both to a conference in Algeria.

02:08:35.000 --> 02:08:46.000
So he was conveniently killed two weeks, two and a half weeks before leaving for Algeria.

02:08:46.000 --> 02:08:55.000
Bill Spina, it's been a real privilege and a long, and thank you for such a thoughtful and extensive commitment.

02:08:55.000 --> 02:09:00.000
Are there any final thoughts, sir?

02:09:00.000 --> 02:09:03.000
Nothing with a thousand things later.

02:09:03.000 --> 02:09:07.000
People I left to help, people I should have mentioned.

02:09:07.000 --> 02:09:10.000
I don't know, thank you.

02:09:10.000 --> 02:09:21.000
But people have been asking me to do a memoir on, and one of the things that I've been lucky enough to meet some great, great people,

02:09:21.000 --> 02:09:38.000
and being able to explain, from my limited viewpoint, the significance of those people that I try to do with Malcolm X, is what make me sit down and write this memoir, called Once Upon a Time.

02:09:39.000 --> 02:09:40.000
Thank you.

02:09:40.000 --> 02:09:50.000
This has been a presentation of the Library of Congress and the Smithsonian National Museum of African American History and Culture.

